  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Elderly patients show different pharmacokinetic and pharmacodynamic variables and usually
      need smaller doses of anaesthetic drugs than younger patients. The purpose of this study was
      to investigate the optimal effect-site concentration of remifentanil for preventing cough
      during emergence in elderly patients under sevoflurane and remifentanil anesthesia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
